WEBVTT

00:02.040 --> 00:03.040
If you don't eat faster...
[ Laughter ]

00:03.040 --> 00:04.250
Jack:
You got to eat fast.

00:04.250 --> 00:06.170
Finish every little bit.

00:06.170 --> 00:07.920
[ Indistinct chatter,
laughter ]

00:07.920 --> 00:09.290
Dre: Kids, come on.

00:09.290 --> 00:10.960
Your grandma's outside,
all right?

00:10.960 --> 00:12.500
You know how much
she hates to wait.

00:12.500 --> 00:15.380
That's for you, sweetie,
and for you.

00:15.380 --> 00:17.500
[ Baby talking ] Bye-bye,
my little munchkin!

00:17.500 --> 00:18.880
[ Normal voice ] And bye,
my little munchkin!

00:18.880 --> 00:20.830
[ Baby talking ] And goodbye
to this munchkin!

00:20.830 --> 00:22.670
And good--

00:22.670 --> 00:24.880
Good day to you,
Mother.

00:24.880 --> 00:26.250
[ Normal voice ]
Good day to you.

00:26.250 --> 00:28.670
All right, little ones,
let's hurry up.

00:28.670 --> 00:30.710
You know Grandma only has
three good hours a day.

00:30.710 --> 00:33.250
Love you guys!
Bye!
Bye.

00:33.250 --> 00:34.830
Love to pieces!
Have a good time!

00:34.830 --> 00:36.170
All:
Hey, Grandma!

00:36.170 --> 00:39.420
[ Door closes ]

00:39.420 --> 00:45.960
[ Piano melody of
Coldplay's "Fix You" plays ]

00:45.960 --> 00:55.170
♪♪

00:55.170 --> 01:04.210
♪♪

01:07.420 --> 01:12.210
♪♪

01:12.210 --> 01:14.620
Dre: Hey, um...

01:17.750 --> 01:20.380
I think I'm gonna head
into the office.

01:24.460 --> 01:25.710
On a Saturday?

01:25.710 --> 01:27.580
You on a...

01:27.580 --> 01:28.670
on a deadline?

01:28.670 --> 01:29.790
Sure.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.750
I-I mean, you know...

01:31.750 --> 01:35.620
Things can always
get in faster, right?

01:35.620 --> 01:37.500
Right.

01:37.500 --> 01:43.540
♪♪

01:43.540 --> 01:46.330
Um...I...

01:46.330 --> 01:47.580
I'm just --
I don't know --

01:47.580 --> 01:51.040
thinking with the kids gone,
maybe we could...

01:51.040 --> 01:53.080
I don't know --
do something.

01:53.080 --> 01:55.210
Brunch? Or something.

01:55.210 --> 01:56.960
Brunch?

01:56.960 --> 01:58.380
Yeah, or something.

01:58.380 --> 02:00.580
I mean, unless you --
you need to work.

02:00.580 --> 02:02.460
No, brunch...

02:02.460 --> 02:04.750
Brunch is cool.

02:04.750 --> 02:06.790
Cool. That'll be fun.
I-I'll go get my purse.

02:06.790 --> 02:07.670
Okay.

02:07.670 --> 02:09.000
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:09.000 --> 02:11.540
Uh...

02:11.540 --> 02:12.960
Are we expecting
someone?

02:12.960 --> 02:14.250
Wait. [ Gasps ]

02:14.250 --> 02:17.420
Oh, my God.
Wait, what is today?

02:17.420 --> 02:20.670
Ohhh.
What?

02:20.670 --> 02:22.420
It's the contractor.

02:22.420 --> 02:23.880
To remodel the kitchen.

02:23.880 --> 02:26.960
Yeah, we scheduled that
a...long ago.

02:26.960 --> 02:29.460
Yeah.

02:29.460 --> 02:32.380
I completely forgot
about that.

02:32.380 --> 02:33.540
I mean,
I can get rid of him.

02:33.540 --> 02:35.040
Mm, no.

02:35.040 --> 02:36.540
No, it's fine.

02:36.540 --> 02:37.830
Are you sure?
Yeah.

02:37.830 --> 02:41.080
Let's -- Let's just
get it over with.

02:41.080 --> 02:44.080
I mean, since
he's already here.

02:44.080 --> 02:45.670
Okay.

02:45.670 --> 02:49.210
Oh, hey, uh...
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:49.210 --> 02:51.500
But like, if, you know,
you decide that

02:51.500 --> 02:53.170
you want to change your mind,
just say so.

02:53.170 --> 02:55.170
Okay.

02:55.170 --> 02:57.500
You know, we got a lot
going on, and...

02:57.500 --> 02:59.500
renovations are
so much work.

02:59.500 --> 03:02.750
Yeah.

03:02.750 --> 03:04.120
They are.

03:07.330 --> 03:10.170
I don't know what
we were even thinking.

03:10.170 --> 03:12.670
♪♪

03:12.670 --> 03:15.250
-Cookies!
-[ Laughing ]

03:15.250 --> 03:17.380
Let me that sonogram again.
[ Laughing ]

03:17.380 --> 03:20.420
This is definitely a boy.
Look at his penis.

03:20.420 --> 03:22.580
That boy is packin' heat!

03:22.580 --> 03:23.830
Dre!
What?

03:23.830 --> 03:26.750
That's his face!

03:26.750 --> 03:28.250
Oh.
[ Laughs ]

03:28.250 --> 03:30.670
Well, he's adorable.
Like his momma.
[ Chuckles ]

03:30.670 --> 03:33.250
Yeah, we do make some
pretty cute babies.

03:33.250 --> 03:35.250
-Mm-hmm.
-Perhaps too many of them?

03:35.250 --> 03:36.790
You guys have a lot
of children.

03:36.790 --> 03:39.750
Yeah. I mean, where's
this one even gonna fit?

03:39.750 --> 03:41.830
Listen, if we're gonna renovate
anything in this house,

03:41.830 --> 03:43.250
we are starting
with the kitchen.

03:43.250 --> 03:44.460
We've been talking about it
forever.

03:44.460 --> 03:45.750
And look. See?
Look at this drawer.

03:45.750 --> 03:47.500
I can't even get it out.
Okay, baby.

03:47.500 --> 03:50.040
Or we could just
fix the drawer.

03:50.040 --> 03:52.620
Or...we could just get
a new kitchen.

03:52.620 --> 03:54.960
Finally!
Whoo!

03:54.960 --> 03:57.710
The blue was a definite
design misstep.

03:57.710 --> 03:59.000
What?
And I mean, come on.

03:59.000 --> 04:01.420
Granite countertops?
Yea--

04:01.420 --> 04:03.540
Pfft. Okay.

04:03.540 --> 04:06.670
Guys, the kitchen is
the heart of the home.

04:06.670 --> 04:08.080
Get your bars up.

04:08.080 --> 04:09.750
Get your bars up, Dre.

04:09.750 --> 04:11.540
-Okay.
-What does that even mean?

04:11.540 --> 04:14.500
[ Hushed voice ] I am not
mad at a new kitchen.

04:14.500 --> 04:15.670
Oooh. Oooh --
Oh, oh, oh!

04:15.670 --> 04:17.210
Hm?

04:17.210 --> 04:18.830
We could design it
together.

04:18.830 --> 04:21.790
You mean converge our flawless
independent styles

04:21.790 --> 04:24.670
into perfect-balanced
dopeness?

04:24.670 --> 04:25.790
Could be fun.

04:25.790 --> 04:27.580
Mm!
Could be fun.

04:27.580 --> 04:29.880
Could be very fun...

04:29.880 --> 04:31.170
[ Sighs ]

04:31.170 --> 04:35.620
♪♪

04:35.620 --> 04:39.580
Well, somewhere in all of this
is our new kitchen.

04:39.580 --> 04:41.380
Yeah, well...

04:41.380 --> 04:44.120
how do we find it?

04:44.120 --> 04:45.960
Just pick what we like.

04:45.960 --> 04:47.210
Can't be that hard.

04:47.210 --> 04:49.380
Mm.

04:49.380 --> 04:52.000
If anyone can knock this out,
it's us.

04:55.580 --> 04:57.790
[ Sighs ]

04:57.790 --> 05:00.330
Well, yeah, they're both cool,
but if you're asking my opinion,

05:00.330 --> 05:03.250
the marble one is doper.

05:03.250 --> 05:05.250
Food and wine stain marble
really easily, though.

05:05.250 --> 05:06.790
Yeah? Well, then
you're just gonna have

05:06.790 --> 05:09.040
to stay on top of the dishes
for a change.

05:13.330 --> 05:15.500
Well, [clears throat]

05:15.500 --> 05:17.120
I was just thinking
we would take, like a --

05:17.120 --> 05:18.540
like a big swing,
you know?

05:18.540 --> 05:20.080
Mm.

05:20.080 --> 05:22.330
You didn't like copper?
Eh, maybe.

05:22.330 --> 05:25.000
But, you know,
I just thought we would go

05:25.000 --> 05:27.330
with something a little bit
more contemporary, you know,

05:27.330 --> 05:30.250
like -- like
a farmhouse style.
Mm-hmm.

05:30.250 --> 05:36.040
You know, with one big,
giant sink bowl.

05:36.040 --> 05:39.120
Yeah, but, you know,
with two sink bowls,

05:39.120 --> 05:41.250
you can put the dirty dishes
on one side

05:41.250 --> 05:44.170
and then move them
to the other side

05:44.170 --> 05:46.500
when you're scrubbing
the food off.

05:46.500 --> 05:49.120
Yeah.

05:49.120 --> 05:50.670
But you
don't do dishes,

05:50.670 --> 05:53.000
so why should you care.
Okay.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.540
You know, look,
let's just, uh...

05:55.540 --> 05:57.540
back away from the sinks
for now.

06:00.380 --> 06:02.420
[ Clears throat ]
Good idea.

06:02.420 --> 06:04.750
Let's just focus
on the overall decor,

06:04.750 --> 06:07.080
and the right sink is
just gonna...

06:07.080 --> 06:09.880
It'll find us.
Exactly.

06:09.880 --> 06:11.420
You know...

06:11.420 --> 06:14.750
I'll guess what
I think you want

06:14.750 --> 06:16.040
your dream kitchen
to look like.

06:16.040 --> 06:17.580
Okay.
And then I'll do you.

06:17.580 --> 06:19.420
Okay.
That'll be fun.

06:19.420 --> 06:21.120
All right, look at
this right here.

06:21.120 --> 06:23.120
Start with that here.

06:26.750 --> 06:28.290
[ Clattering ]

06:28.290 --> 06:31.880
Yeah, I think
you'll like that.

06:31.880 --> 06:33.500
Yeah, it's nice.

06:33.500 --> 06:35.040
If you --
If you like that.

06:35.040 --> 06:36.380
[ Scoffs ]

06:36.380 --> 06:38.920
Okay.
You don't like it.

06:38.920 --> 06:41.380
It's a little bohemian
for my taste.

06:41.380 --> 06:42.830
Well, I thought
you liked bohemian.

06:42.830 --> 06:44.500
I do not.

06:44.500 --> 06:46.540
[ Clattering ]

06:46.540 --> 06:48.540
♪♪

06:48.540 --> 06:49.710
Okay, my turn.

06:49.710 --> 06:51.250
Okay.

06:51.250 --> 06:54.210
Easy, easy, easy.
I got this.

06:56.380 --> 07:00.080
Boom.

07:00.080 --> 07:04.620
♪♪

07:04.620 --> 07:06.120
Green is
your favorite color.

07:06.120 --> 07:07.500
[ Scoffs ]
It's not.

07:07.500 --> 07:09.120
Oh.

07:09.120 --> 07:10.380
Well, you know,
it doesn't matter.

07:10.380 --> 07:11.920
I mean, I don't --
I don't even know

07:11.920 --> 07:13.420
what my favorite color is.

07:13.420 --> 07:16.750
It's purple.

07:16.750 --> 07:17.920
Yeah.

07:17.920 --> 07:20.620
Okay, you can do this.
"Tandem."

07:20.620 --> 07:22.120
Trailer!

07:22.120 --> 07:25.000
It's a [bleep] bike,
Bruce!

07:25.000 --> 07:26.920
The keyword is "bike."

07:26.920 --> 07:28.710
[ Indistinct squabbling ]

07:28.710 --> 07:30.880
Dre: Bruce, sit.
Okay, it's our turn!
Dre and Bow!

07:30.880 --> 07:32.500
-Okay.
-Okay, babe.

07:32.500 --> 07:34.250
I'm gon' give you
some clues.

07:34.250 --> 07:36.710
Give 'em to me, baby.
All right. And go.

07:36.710 --> 07:37.830
Makes you hungry.

07:37.830 --> 07:39.080
Cartoon pie.
Next.

07:39.080 --> 07:40.790
Makes you cry.
Violins. Next.

07:40.790 --> 07:42.580
It's fun to put stuff
in your...?

07:42.580 --> 07:43.880
Butt! Next!

07:43.880 --> 07:45.920
The lady.
Adult braces! Next!

07:45.920 --> 07:47.500
Yuck.
Sparkling wine! Next!

07:47.500 --> 07:48.960
Uh-oh. Uh-oh.

07:48.960 --> 07:50.420
Oh, hold on.
Uh-oh.

07:50.420 --> 07:51.830
Um...

07:51.830 --> 07:52.920
Um...

07:52.920 --> 07:54.040
Quantum physics!

07:54.040 --> 07:55.580
Yes!
Yeah!

07:55.580 --> 07:57.040
Time, time, time, time, time,
time, time, time!

07:57.040 --> 07:59.580
[ Dre and Rainbow laughing ]

07:59.580 --> 08:01.880
Mm!

08:01.880 --> 08:03.120
That was, uh...

08:03.120 --> 08:05.170
That was very impressive.
H-How'd you guys do that?

08:05.170 --> 08:06.710
-We know each other...
-Mm-hmm.

08:06.710 --> 08:07.580
...really well.

08:07.580 --> 08:09.960
Inside and out.
Ah.

08:09.960 --> 08:14.880
♪♪

08:14.880 --> 08:17.670
Well, I'm, uh...

08:17.670 --> 08:20.420
I'm gonna go into the office
and get a little work done.

08:20.420 --> 08:22.000
Yep.

08:22.000 --> 08:23.120
You got that deadline,
so...

08:23.120 --> 08:24.460
Mm-hmm.

08:24.460 --> 08:26.000
Rainbow: We can do
all this later.

08:26.000 --> 08:28.830
Yeah, definitely.
Yep.

08:28.830 --> 08:30.120
It's a date.

08:30.120 --> 08:32.540
Definitely.

08:32.540 --> 08:39.710
♪♪

08:44.710 --> 08:48.040
Oh, good. [ Sing-songy]
Lunch is here!

08:48.040 --> 08:49.670
[ Normal voice ]
Where's my sandwich?

08:49.670 --> 08:51.920
[ Muffled ]
You mean this one?

08:55.330 --> 08:57.790
Sorry.
I thought it was an extra.

08:57.790 --> 08:59.830
I can order you
another one.

08:59.830 --> 09:02.330
Junior, it took two hours
for this to get here.

09:02.330 --> 09:04.380
Just forget it.

09:04.380 --> 09:05.880
I just want
my kitchen back.

09:05.880 --> 09:08.620
Why is the refrigerator
in the family room?

09:08.620 --> 09:12.170
See, this why they say don't
stay at home during renovations.

09:12.170 --> 09:13.830
This is why I said
I wanted to stay in a hotel.

09:13.830 --> 09:16.250
I cannot live like this.

09:16.250 --> 09:19.170
[ Sighs ]

09:19.170 --> 09:20.250
Rainbow: Baby?
Dre: Hey, baby.

09:20.250 --> 09:21.580
I'm hungry.
Oooh.

09:21.580 --> 09:23.170
Should we go pick up the kids
from your mom's

09:23.170 --> 09:24.670
and then grab dinner?

09:24.670 --> 09:27.040
Don't trip, my little
white-chocolate chip.

09:27.040 --> 09:28.250
[ Laughs ]
All right?

09:28.250 --> 09:30.540
Big Daddy got you dinner.

09:30.540 --> 09:32.380
What did --
No. Unh-unh.

09:32.380 --> 09:33.670
No!
Yes! Uh-huh!

09:33.670 --> 09:34.880
I am not eating
that stuff.

09:34.880 --> 09:36.670
It is so bad
for you.

09:36.670 --> 09:38.670
Ramen, milady?

09:38.670 --> 09:40.500
Ahhhh!

09:40.500 --> 09:42.210
I love it so much!

09:42.210 --> 09:43.330
I'ma get noodle music.

09:43.330 --> 09:44.380
You get noodle music.

09:44.380 --> 09:46.580
Noodle music.
[ Static crackling ]

09:46.580 --> 09:48.460
[ Coldplay's "The Scientist"
plays ]
Oh, look at that.
I'm like a DJ, huh?

09:48.460 --> 09:50.040
Come on, get up on the counter.
Okay, you got to help me.

09:50.040 --> 09:51.210
Okay, hold on.
Ready?

09:51.210 --> 09:52.500
Uh-huh.
One, two, three, go!
Oh, God!

09:52.500 --> 09:54.540
[ Groaning ] Whoa!
Don't slide off.

09:54.540 --> 09:57.750
♪ Come up to meet you ♪
Okay. [Laughs] I won't.

09:57.750 --> 10:01.080
♪ Tell you I'm sorry ♪
Yes.

10:01.080 --> 10:07.170
♪ You don't know
how lovely you are ♪

10:07.170 --> 10:12.620
♪ Nobody said it was easy ♪

10:12.620 --> 10:14.080
Okay. Ready?

10:14.080 --> 10:17.830
♪ It's such a shame
for us to part ♪
Go, go.

10:17.830 --> 10:20.420
Get it off my lips.

10:20.420 --> 10:25.210
♪ Nobody said it was easy ♪
[ Both laugh ]

10:25.210 --> 10:27.080
I love you.

10:27.080 --> 10:32.420
I love you so much
♪ No one ever said
it would be this hard ♪

10:32.420 --> 10:35.040
Mm!
[ Chuckles ]

10:35.040 --> 10:40.170
♪ Oh, take me back
to the start ♪

10:42.080 --> 10:43.580
You got it?
Yeah.

10:43.580 --> 10:45.500
All right,
one last time.

10:45.500 --> 10:46.250
Bam.

10:46.250 --> 10:47.710
Rainbow:
It's cold.

10:47.710 --> 10:48.830
It's sexy.

10:48.830 --> 10:50.460
N-- [ Scoffs ]
You know what?

10:50.460 --> 10:52.120
Just tell me what sink
you want.

10:52.120 --> 10:53.460
I told you what I want.

10:53.460 --> 10:55.170
You're not listening.

10:55.170 --> 10:57.500
♪♪

10:57.500 --> 10:59.210
It's just like the flowers
all over again.

10:59.210 --> 11:01.790
[ Clears throat ]

11:01.790 --> 11:03.380
What about flowers?

11:03.380 --> 11:06.210
I told you I like flowers,
but...

11:06.210 --> 11:09.330
you don't listen
to what I want.

11:09.330 --> 11:11.250
You want to know
why I don't bring flowers?

11:11.250 --> 11:12.830
Mm-hmm.

11:12.830 --> 11:14.710
Dre: Okay.
Keep your eyes closed!

11:14.710 --> 11:15.540
Rainbow:
They're closed!

11:15.540 --> 11:18.330
Open them!
Check it out!

11:18.330 --> 11:21.620
Prepare...to be swept...
off your feet.

11:21.620 --> 11:23.790
I'm ready. [ Screams ]
Voilà!

11:26.170 --> 11:28.170
That is hilarious.
Mm-hmm.

11:28.170 --> 11:30.620
That is hilarious!

11:30.620 --> 11:33.670
Oh, my God! You went through
all these Post-its...

11:33.670 --> 11:36.250
Uh-huh.
...so that I could
get to one little rose!

11:36.250 --> 11:37.620
[ Chuckling ]
[ Laughs ]

11:37.620 --> 11:39.040
I know, huh?

11:39.040 --> 11:40.880
Oh, my God, we have
the same sense of humor!

11:40.880 --> 11:42.750
That is so funny.
It was like --
Wasn't a joke.

11:42.750 --> 11:44.210
It was like
all this buildup.

11:44.210 --> 11:45.960
All this buildup,
and I was like,

11:45.960 --> 11:47.290
"Oh, my God,
this Post-it!"

11:47.290 --> 11:50.580
I obviously didn't mean
to embarrass you.

11:50.580 --> 11:51.790
I thought we were joking.

11:51.790 --> 11:54.460
I-I...

11:54.460 --> 11:55.670
I...

11:55.670 --> 11:58.380
I'm sorry.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.540
I appreciate your apology.

12:00.540 --> 12:01.620
[ Sighs ]

12:01.620 --> 12:05.420
♪♪

12:05.420 --> 12:08.620
You could've gotten it
a long time ago.

12:08.620 --> 12:10.380
If you hadn't held it in
this whole time,

12:10.380 --> 12:13.830
just carrying around your anger
like you do.

12:13.830 --> 12:15.540
[ Sighing ]
Oh, here we go.

12:15.540 --> 12:16.880
What?

12:16.880 --> 12:19.580
Bow, I do not always
carry around anger!

12:19.580 --> 12:21.540
Okay, Dre.

12:21.540 --> 12:22.710
Okay.

12:22.710 --> 12:25.000
You just did.

12:25.000 --> 12:26.380
Like -- Like when
I picked that movie.

12:26.380 --> 12:28.750
What?

12:28.750 --> 12:30.750
Dre, a couple
of months ago,

12:30.750 --> 12:33.000
you got so angry

12:33.000 --> 12:34.500
when I picked that movie
that you didn't like,

12:34.500 --> 12:36.080
and you haven't let me
pick a movie ever since.

12:36.080 --> 12:37.750
You said it was
supposed to be good.

12:37.750 --> 12:41.500
I said I heard the movie
was good.

12:41.500 --> 12:45.580
No, you said, and I quote,
"Jennifer Lawrence? Oscar bait."

12:45.580 --> 12:47.080
Whatever!

12:47.080 --> 12:48.670
It was one bad movie.

12:48.670 --> 12:51.960
That you dragged me to on
my only free Saturday in months.

12:51.960 --> 12:54.330
I dragged you to it?
Really, Dre?

12:54.330 --> 12:57.290
So now us spending time together
is me dragging you places?

12:57.290 --> 12:58.540
Look, all you had
to do was admit

12:58.540 --> 12:59.960
that you knew nothing
about the movie,

12:59.960 --> 13:01.250
and we could've seen
something else.

13:01.250 --> 13:04.460
But no, you can never admit
to not knowing anything

13:04.460 --> 13:07.040
because you have
to know everything.

13:07.040 --> 13:08.290
Just like a few years ago.

13:08.290 --> 13:09.830
Oh, you're bringing up
old arguments?

13:09.830 --> 13:11.170
Yes. I am.
Okay.

13:11.170 --> 13:12.750
Is that a problem?
Yes, it's a problem, Dre!

13:12.750 --> 13:15.000
'Cause I have no idea
what we're fighting about!

13:15.000 --> 13:17.790
I literally have no idea what
you want from me right now!

13:17.790 --> 13:20.670
I don't want anything from you!
I was just trying to buy a sink!

13:20.670 --> 13:23.380
[ Sighing ]
Oh, my God.

13:23.380 --> 13:25.170
And you go all in
about flowers.

13:25.170 --> 13:26.210
Oh, so now this argument's
my fault?

13:26.210 --> 13:27.710
Yes.
This is my fault?

13:27.710 --> 13:28.880
Yes, it's your fault.

13:28.880 --> 13:30.790
And it's all good,
because according to you,

13:30.790 --> 13:32.330
everything else
is my fault.

13:32.330 --> 13:34.420
I always admit when
I don't know something.

13:34.420 --> 13:36.210
When you're being a know-it-all?
All the time.

13:36.210 --> 13:37.250
Did you just call me
arrogant?

13:37.250 --> 13:38.170
You are.

13:38.170 --> 13:39.580
Me?! Arrogant?!
Oh, my God.

13:39.580 --> 13:40.830
Okay? What about it?!

13:40.830 --> 13:41.880
[ Indistinct shouting ]

13:41.880 --> 13:44.460
[ Pounding noise ]

13:44.460 --> 13:46.830
[ Breathing heavily ]

13:46.830 --> 13:49.830
♪♪

13:49.830 --> 13:52.750
Oh, my God.

13:52.750 --> 13:54.500
It's Jack's footprint.

13:54.500 --> 13:56.540
Yeah.

13:56.540 --> 13:58.920
I almost forgot
about that.

13:58.920 --> 14:01.830
He stepped in...
finger paint.

14:01.830 --> 14:09.920
♪♪

14:09.920 --> 14:13.290
You can pick the sink.

14:13.290 --> 14:15.170
Do what you want
in the kitchen.

14:15.170 --> 14:17.540
I don't care anymore.

14:17.540 --> 14:21.960
♪♪

14:27.420 --> 14:30.330
♪♪

14:30.330 --> 14:31.210
Young Dre: Mama?

14:31.210 --> 14:32.670
What's wrong, baby?

14:32.670 --> 14:34.670
Wh-Why you sleeping
out here?

14:34.670 --> 14:39.250
Oh, I uh...

14:39.250 --> 14:40.960
You and Pops had
a fight, huh?

14:40.960 --> 14:43.790
Oh, sweetie, we just hit
a bit of a rough patch.

14:43.790 --> 14:46.210
That's all.

14:46.210 --> 14:48.670
You come on over here
and sit down.

14:53.580 --> 14:57.960
Sometimes it's hard
for adults...

14:57.960 --> 15:01.040
to share a life.

15:01.040 --> 15:02.380
Why?

15:02.380 --> 15:06.790
Well, me and your daddy
got married so young.

15:06.790 --> 15:09.750
It's not easy.

15:09.750 --> 15:14.080
You make this insane choice
to love someone for who they are

15:14.080 --> 15:17.420
before you've even figured out
who you are yourself,

15:17.420 --> 15:20.920
let alone who either of you
are gonna grow up to become,

15:20.920 --> 15:23.460
you know?

15:23.460 --> 15:25.960
Who did you and Pops
grow up to become?

15:25.960 --> 15:28.080
Different.

15:28.080 --> 15:31.000
Y-Yeah,
but in -- in a good way.

15:31.000 --> 15:32.750
Sometimes.

15:32.750 --> 15:34.960
Sometimes not.

15:36.210 --> 15:40.500
But we're choosing
to see the good.

15:40.500 --> 15:43.580
Marriage is
about choices.

15:43.580 --> 15:47.830
You got to keep
choosing each other.

15:47.830 --> 15:50.540
Even when you're not sure
it's the right choice.

15:50.540 --> 15:53.460
♪♪

15:53.460 --> 15:54.750
Do you and Pops love
each other?

15:54.750 --> 15:56.710
Oh, yes.

15:56.710 --> 15:59.330
[ Chuckles ]

15:59.330 --> 16:01.620
But the trick is...

16:01.620 --> 16:07.170
to keep falling in love
with each other.

16:07.170 --> 16:11.460
Falling in love
seems rough.

16:11.460 --> 16:14.670
It's the best thing
you'll ever do.

16:14.670 --> 16:16.380
♪♪

16:16.380 --> 16:19.380
You just got to be careful that
the person you fall in love with

16:19.380 --> 16:22.920
is worth it to you.

16:22.920 --> 16:25.420
Okay?

16:25.420 --> 16:27.830
Okay.

16:27.830 --> 16:31.790
♪♪

16:31.790 --> 16:35.620
[ Alarm beeping ]

16:35.620 --> 16:38.210
[ Sighs deeply ]

16:38.210 --> 16:41.330
♪♪

16:41.330 --> 16:42.750
[ Yawns ]

16:42.750 --> 16:48.710
[ Indistinct chatter
in distance ]

16:48.710 --> 16:51.210
Diane: Whoa, Dad.
You're up early again.

16:51.210 --> 16:53.920
Yes, I am.
Who wants Pop-Tarts?

16:53.920 --> 16:56.080
[ Sighs ] I love a Tart
as much as the next man,

16:56.080 --> 16:58.080
but five mornings
in a row?

16:58.080 --> 16:59.290
Morning, guys.

16:59.290 --> 17:01.460
-Morning.
-Good morning.

17:11.710 --> 17:14.120
♪♪

17:14.120 --> 17:15.500
I'm Dre.

17:15.500 --> 17:17.710
Rainbow.

17:17.710 --> 17:19.960
[ Whimpers ]

17:19.960 --> 17:21.040
Thank God.
[ Chuckling ]

17:21.040 --> 17:22.080
Oh, thank God.
Bam!

17:22.080 --> 17:23.330
Oh...thank God.

17:23.330 --> 17:26.460
Kiss your bride!
[ All cheer ]

17:26.460 --> 17:28.580
I love what I have
with you.

17:28.580 --> 17:29.670
Works for me.

17:29.670 --> 17:36.500
♪♪

17:36.500 --> 17:37.620
We're pregnant.

17:37.620 --> 17:39.460
[ Laughs ]

17:39.460 --> 17:42.290
♪♪

17:42.290 --> 17:43.750
[ Heart beat ]
[ All gasp ]

17:43.750 --> 17:45.670
My God.
[ Laughter ]

17:45.670 --> 17:48.460
♪♪

17:48.460 --> 17:49.540
[ Bell dings ]
Oh!

17:49.540 --> 17:52.120
Uh-huh, if you could
just, uh...

17:52.120 --> 17:53.620
take your jeans off
right now.

17:53.620 --> 17:56.250
Okay, give me some.
Give me some.

17:56.250 --> 17:57.620
I can see him!
He's here, babe!

17:57.620 --> 18:00.000
He's here!
Oh, it's Devante!

18:00.000 --> 18:05.420
♪♪

18:05.420 --> 18:07.620
Hey.

18:07.620 --> 18:09.250
Hey.

18:15.500 --> 18:16.460
Hey.

18:16.460 --> 18:18.380
Hey.

18:18.380 --> 18:22.710
I got midnight snack
for the both of us.

18:22.710 --> 18:25.670
Ramen, milady?

18:25.670 --> 18:28.620
Oh. No thanks.

18:28.620 --> 18:29.880
That stuff is
terrible for you.

18:29.880 --> 18:32.710
It's filled with sodium.
I can't eat those.

18:32.710 --> 18:34.460
[ Clears throat ]

18:39.670 --> 18:40.880
My bad.

18:48.170 --> 18:49.080
W--

18:49.080 --> 18:53.540
Dre...

18:53.540 --> 18:55.380
What?

18:55.380 --> 18:57.380
[ Sighs ]

18:57.380 --> 18:59.380
[ Inhales deeply, sighs ]

19:07.120 --> 19:09.080
We can't keep
doing this.

19:17.170 --> 19:18.790
I...

19:20.880 --> 19:24.120
...think, um...

19:29.420 --> 19:32.040
...we need space.

19:34.420 --> 19:36.420
[ Scoffs ]

19:41.500 --> 19:43.670
I think you're right.

19:43.670 --> 19:46.540
[ Coldplay's "Fix You" plays ]

19:46.540 --> 19:51.380
Well, that's the first thing
we've managed to agree on...

19:51.380 --> 19:52.670
in a while.

19:52.670 --> 19:56.500
♪♪

19:56.500 --> 20:03.460
♪ When you try your best,
but you don't succeed ♪

20:03.460 --> 20:10.420
♪ When you get what you want,
but not what you need ♪
So, uh...

20:10.420 --> 20:16.460
♪ You when you feel so tired,
but you can't sleep ♪

20:16.460 --> 20:23.120
♪ Stuck in reverse ♪

20:23.120 --> 20:26.580
♪♪

20:26.580 --> 20:33.960
♪ Lights will guide you home ♪
How the hell did we get here?

20:33.960 --> 20:40.540
[ Voice breaking ]
I don't know.
♪ And ignite your bones ♪

20:40.540 --> 20:46.960
♪ And I will try to fix you ♪

20:53.170 --> 20:55.170
I'm the oldest!
I get the biggest room!

20:55.170 --> 20:57.380
No fair, Zoey!

20:57.380 --> 20:58.580
[ Dre and Rainbow laugh ]

20:58.580 --> 21:02.210
Oh, babe, I can't believe
all of this is ours.

21:02.210 --> 21:03.750
Me either.

21:03.750 --> 21:04.790
[ Sighs deeply ]

21:04.790 --> 21:05.790
This is crazy.

21:05.790 --> 21:07.210
Crazy.

21:07.210 --> 21:09.040
♪♪

21:09.040 --> 21:11.710
How the hell did
we get here?

21:11.710 --> 21:15.580
I don't know.

21:15.580 --> 21:17.580
[ Chuckles ]
